Subject: Attention Relation Contracts

Description: Typed relation contracts for focus, periphery, correlation, causation, and narrative digestion.

& [AttentionRelationContracts] is the relation vocabulary for SOP-HG attention movement
  + [attends] is focus directly attends a node
  + [orbits] is periphery keeps a node available around focus
  + [correlates] is two or more nodes share features, terms, pressure, or heat
  + [causes] is one node changes, enables, blocks, or explains another with evidence
  + [draws_attention] is a periphery node gains enough relation weight to pull toward focus
  + [digests] is narrative is written into a subject layer
  + [bounds] is outside constrains what the relation cannot prove

& [CorrelationVsCausationBoundary] is the rule separating association from cause
  + [correlation] is shared depth, shared terms, repeated touch, or proximity in a thought-current
  + [causation] is supported change relation, enabling relation, blocking relation, or explicit reason relation
  + [hypothesis] is possible causation without enough evidence
  + [outside] is unsupported causal story

  = must: record correlation and causation as different edge kinds
  = must: label causal hypotheses before evidence is sufficient
  = must: allow one hyperedge to carry both correlation and causal roles when evidence supports both
  - never: promote association into cause by heat alone
